The paper discusses algorithms for proximity search and clustering on large datasets, which are fundamental problems in data structures (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and multimedia (cs.MM). The focus on binary coding and matrix sketching techniques also suggests a potential fit with these sub-categories.
